body:
@ijuma thanks for taking a look. You're right, ACLs could be used to restrict this. Though in a cluster that wasn't locked down, allowing anyone to produce to the __consumer_offsets topic could cause unexpected behaviour.

I guess the question is mostly why such a back door exists in the first place. 

If we are to remove it, it seems a shame that a three line code change to remove an undocumented backdoor requires a KIP!

Assuming we want to plug this hole, are we sure we want the overhead of going down that route?  

@junrao any background and opinions much appreciated!
